reviews.review_text: Great place, great selection of treats and Raw & Dry Food. My number 1 choice to shop for our pets.
I take my dog to have a bath her. It is always available- no wait- it is clean and they are very friendly.
Best products. Friendly and helpful staff. $10 dog wash. My cat especially enjoyed the surf n turf pate by purrrfect bistro and my dog went cray on the beef rib bones.
Really knowledgeable staff! After trying 4 different kibbles from PetSmart:/ My picky puppy finally ate all his food for the first time after getting the recommended one from one of their brands.
Great quality dog food. Convenient washing station, shampoo&conditioner provided. Location is great.
Great store with awesome staff. SO friendly and helpful. They have an awesome dog wash there with lots of soap, towels and treats.
Great pet store and great staff.  Love this pet store and my dog loves the doggy wash.  Always have our food in stock and even able to get us a special order jacket.

Love this pet food store. Always nice and friendly. They dont even seem to mind kids coming in just to look at pet toys. Haha. Weird hours on Sundays though. May want to call before you go to make sure they are open.
Even though my dog hates getting washed, this is a good place to take your dirty pooch after a hike or visit to the beach to get rid of that stinky dog smell
My little baby Girl loves to get her baths done at Petvalu after a long day at the beach

Their staff are very helpful and they have a wide range of products. I know with the supply chain issues sometimes they dont have what Im looking for, but they will order it in for me. They have free parking as well.

For a small Bosleys store they provide 5 star service to their self service dog wash station!  I called them towards the end of the day to see if I can use their self serve wash station and they took my name & number, asked me what shampoo I wanted to use and the # of towels I needed. As it was my first time, they recommended a shampoo for me and advised that 3 towels should be sufficient. They also asked what treats I needed?!? ( Chicken, beef or lamb!) When I arrived, everything was laid out for us. The treats came in handy as it was what helped me through the blow drying of my mini aussie. She hated the dryer but loved the treats!

Wow, some pretty bad reviews of the staff here...which surprises me as Ive always had pretty friendly and helpful staff experiences here. Hence, my review. I think theyre shortstaffed, so sometimes staff will be occupied with other customers  - but, overall I find the staff really helpful and kind.

I went in today to get some help for my rescue pup that I just got - he hasnt been eating anything - even treats. Two very sweet female workers helped me get him to eat, and helped me with a car harness. They were also so sweet to my pup, he was very happy. Thank you ladies, great experience!

Staff is very kind and welcoming. The store didnt have in stock the filter for my fountain and they ordered it without asking anything in advance. With the COVID in full swing, this store also organized local delivery, real life saver!

A perfect showcase of the North American 70 Billion ++ $$ pet industry. My family is keeping dogs for 200+ years and all what we bought during these years were a leash and a collar. In today world dogs require teeth cleaning and some of my friends are spending $500 to $600 for a session. There is more variety in this store than in a seven eleven store. :) Anyhow, the staff is friendly and polite.
This seasons  winter apparel for dogs are  styling and a bit pricey  My puppy left happy with a affordable small size chew stick...

Went to this store for the first time to use the dog Wash. Some of the other reviews werent great but staff was super friendly when I went. Def a good deal for washing your dog esp if youre like me and have a giant floofer with tons of hair. Good shampoo selection and its easy to tie your dog up in the tub. The dryer air is not warm as someone stated which is good since dogs actually overheat easily and shouldnt be dried with hot air. Will definitely be visiting again since it saves me trying to wash/brush my dog at my house which is an ordeal.

This Bosley s is my preferred location because of its dog washing station that offers 30 and 60 min appointments, shampoo/conditioner, towels, dryer, brushes, and a generous serving of treats. The friendly and helpful staff are an added bonus that keep us coming back.

Bosleys is a really good pet store. I never really went into there much except since my cats began fighting six months ago, and Ive had to go in there for things to calm them down. Staff have always been really helpful and informative. Their prices are average

Love it!  Shop there all the time.  The Manager Chantelle and staff are great - very helpful and friendly. Store is always clean and tidy.  Especially love the dog-washing stations that were just installed.
Great store staff, love that they have a dog wash and a huge selection of pet food. I almost wish I was a cat, havent seen better cat trees/scratchers     Great location nestled right next to Tims.
Great selection, really nice staff. Its a small shop, so if youre looking for specific kibble, call ahead. But they also seem willing to order most things in!
There was a beautiful lady who paid for my sandwich that works there. Your staff is so kind thank you Bosley staff you rock merry Christmas
Great pet store with great variety, of cat and dog food. They also have a pet washing center.

Was in there today, they had everything. It was clean. The shelves were fully stocked. The staff was friendly. :) Also, the short haired girl who treated the other reviewer doesnt work there anymore! I would strongly recommend this store.

Bosleys feels like a great neighborhood pet store even though its a large chain with lots of great pet products and foods. They also have a dog washing station to self wash your Fido with 2 tubs available. Great for doggy owners that have a muddy day at Charleson dog park next to the seawall about 10 minute walk away. You can walk from the dog park across busy 6th Ave on the Laurel St  pedestrian overpass to get there. Has parking too.
We went in and were greeted very nicely by Jasmine! Had a great time and left satisfied! 10/10 will shop here again.
The cats liked the food.
Lovely little store.  The employee was very helpful and friendly.
Nice pet store to shop! Also find what your pet need, friendly staffs! No problem to find parking.Enjoy the 10% senior discount last Thursday every month.

Good selection of food and accoutrements for all kinds of pets. Ask about frequent buyer programs. Acana dry dog food buy 12 bags, get 1 free.  Dog wash is every 8th bath free. Register with your phone #
You can find everything for your pet here ! Friendly staff and also really good working hrs.
Employees here are so helpful and friendly. Prices are average - toys a bit on the expensive side but alright if you catch it on a sale. They sell high end foods.
Well organized store with very friendly staff!
This little pet store is absolutely adorable. They have great products and a wide variety of organic options for my fur babies!
Friendly staff. Best place to wash your dog. They supply everything, even dog treats.
Its the only place that I can get my favorite chicken pate... I mean for my cat.
Great, friendly and helpful staff and always have the food I feed our dog in stock.
Nice bathtubs for washing your pup. They provide the towel, shampoo, towel, collars (for washing)/vacuum and brush. Cant beat that.
Great pet store, parking out front, they have a wide selection of cat toys, usually friendly staff.
Bosley is smaller, but much more personable - with TLC
Competitive prices with other pet food stores, very good selection of products and great staff
Friendly staff and great service. Much better than Pet Smart on West 2nd.
They always have my dogs food in stock and the staff are super friendly!
Nice store and my dog loves getting a treat when he visits.
They have a great selection of stuff for my dogs! Excellent service
literally the nicest staff. super helpful and understanding. will be coming back regularly :)
very helpful and friendly service..layout of products done so easy to find what you are looking for
Nice and helpful staff. Good dog washing room.
New manager was super helpful. Great experience shopping there!
The staff is wonderful!  Always a friendly smile and good advice.
Bosleys is the best pet food and supply place around. The staff are amazing
Great place to wash your dog
Friendly helpful staff and lots of healthy cat food to choose from.
Great customer service, friendly staff, love this location.
Friendly staff and always have what I am looking for my dog.
Friendly staff and welcoming of questions. Always helpful.
Friendly staff, reasonable prices and free parking.
Staff always friendly and knowledgeable
Great staff, good selection
Great customer service. Staff are terrific.
Great selection for all your pet needs
Good stock. They had what I was looking for.
Good service, they always have good specials.
Very helpful always
Best dog wash station ever
Super helpful staff with engraving tag
Great help with everything! Very friendly!
Great place, lovely staff.
Store kitty pleases me
staff is friendly and go the extra mile
This location has a dog Wash area
Great selection at this location.
Great place to wash your dog!
Staff is great!!
Best bosleys I know.
Best place to wash the pooch
